    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> It does not work for `expect.any(SearchParameters)` alone?\r\n\r\nnope: \r\n\r\n```\r\n TypeError: any() expects to be passed a constructor function. Please pass one or use anything() to match any object.\r\n\r\n      186 |             }),\r\n      187 |             instantSearchInstance: expect.any(InstantSearch),\r\n    > 188 |             state: expect.any(SearchParameters)\r\n          |                           ^\r\n      189 |             // state: expect.objectContaining({\r\n      190 |             //   another: {\r\n      191 |             //     config: 'parameter',\r\n\r\n      at new Any (node_modules/expect/build/asymmetricMatchers.js:27:13)\r\n      at Function.any (node_modules/expect/build/asymmetricMatchers.js:250:31)\r\n      at Object.any (src/lib/__tests__/InstantSearch-test.js:188:27)\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think it might be because it's from `node_modules` 🤔 ",
